atom in an atom trap

00:02:13.410 --> 00:02:14.920
or an ion in an ion trap.

00:02:14.920 --> 00:02:16.770
And you don't have
to create the vacuum.

00:02:16.770 --> 00:02:17.660
It's there.

00:02:17.660 --> 00:02:19.890
Every time you look
at it, it's there.

00:02:19.890 --> 00:02:21.800
And you can excite
it with the laser.

00:02:21.800 --> 00:02:24.305
It has a spectrum
similar to atoms.

00:02:24.305 --> 00:02:28.770
It has spin
structure So you have

00:02:28.770 --> 00:02:30.350
these vacancies in diamond.

00:02:33.820 --> 00:02:35.980
So these are little
quantum dots.

00:02:35.980 --> 00:02:37.960
But now you have two problems.

00:02:37.960 --> 00:02:43.960
One is you want to collect
the light emitted by them.

00:02:43.960 --> 00:02:49.930
And what is best is to mill a
lens right into the material.

00:02:49.930 --> 00:02:51.525
So this is the diamond material.

00:02:51.525 --> 00:02:52.880
A lens is milled.

00:02:52.880 --> 00:02:55.160
And that already gives
some [? culmination ?]

00:02:55.160 --> 00:02:57.360
of the light emitted by it.

00:02:57.360 --> 00:03:00.020
But the bit problem
until recently

00:03:00.020 --> 00:03:03.600
has been when you create
those some people call it

00:03:03.600 --> 00:03:05.140
artificial atoms.

00:03:05.140 --> 00:03:07.970
Every atom is a
little bit different,

00:03:07.970 --> 00:03:12.220
because it experience a
slightly different environment.

00:03:12.220 --> 00:03:16.350
A crystal has strain, so if you
have seemingly two identical

00:03:16.350 --> 00:03:22.760
defects in a diamond
crystal, the two defects

00:03:22.760 --> 00:03:24.750
will have a
resonance line, which

00:03:24.750 --> 00:03:26.810
is a few gigahertz difference.

00:03:26.810 --> 00:03:29.060
You would say, well, maybe
it's just [? apart ?] in 10

00:03:29.060 --> 00:03:32.780
to the 5, but it means the
photons are distinguishable.

00:03:32.780 --> 00:03:35.970
So if you want to do
entanglement by having two such

00:03:35.970 --> 00:03:40.240
artificial atoms emitting a
photon onto a beam splitter,

00:03:40.240 --> 00:03:43.020
and then by performing
a measurement we project

00:03:43.020 --> 00:03:46.180
the atoms into Bell state-- I
hope you all remember what we

00:03:46.180 --> 00:03:49.770
discussed for the trapped ions--
then you have to make sure that

00:03:49.770 --> 00:03:53.930
fundamentally, those photons
cannot be distinguished.

00:03:53.930 --> 00:04:00.490
And the trick here is that
they put on some electrodes.

00:04:00.490 --> 00:04:05.550
And by adding an
electric field, they

00:04:05.550 --> 00:04:07.790
